I found the problem! Look at line 542-547:

```kotlin
cardsListView.setOnItemClickListener { _: AdapterView<*>?, view: View?, position: Int, _: Long ->
    if (isInMultiSelectMode) {
        // click on whole cell triggers select
        val cb = view!!.findViewById<CheckBox>(R.id.card_checkbox)
        cb.toggle()
        viewModel.selectRowAtPosition(position)  // BUG: This always ADDS, never toggles!
```

And at line 564-567 (long click):
```kotlin
// click on whole cell triggers select
val cb = view!!.findViewById<CheckBox>(R.id.card_checkbox)
cb.toggle()
viewModel.toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position)  // This is correct - toggles!
```

The issue is that when clicking on a card in multiselect mode, the code calls `selectRowAtPosition` which only ADDS to the selection (never removes). But it toggles the checkbox visually with `cb.toggle()`.

Looking at the ViewModel:
```kotlin
fun selectRowAtPosition(pos: Int) {
    if (_selectedRows.add(cards[pos])) {  // Only adds, never removes
        refreshSelectedRowsFlow()
    }
}

fun toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position: Int) {  // This properly toggles
    val card = cards[position]
    if (_selectedRows.contains(card)) {
        _selectedRows.remove(card)
    } else {
        _selectedRows.add(card)
    }
    refreshSelectedRowsFlow()
}
```

So the fix is simple: change line 547 from `viewModel.selectRowAtPosition(position)` to `viewModel.toggleRowSelectionAtPosition(position)`.

Let me read the CardBrowser.kt file around that area to make the exact change.

